  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Partial Nephrectomy is the standard care for small (&lt;4 cm) renal tumors. Despite the
      expanding use of laparoscopic approach, debate exist regarding the short and long term
      outcomes compared to the open approach. Our goal is to perform a prospective randomized trial
      to compare these methods
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
